{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"bpftime","page":{"layout":"document","title":"Compile Once, Run Everywhere(CO-RE)","description":"You can simply provide the external BTF for userspace host application in your eBPF program:","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<p>You can simply provide the external BTF for userspace host application in your eBPF program:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    LIBBPF_OPTS</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(bpf_object_open_opts , opts,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    );</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    LIBBPF_OPTS</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(bpf_uprobe_opts, uprobe_opts);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (argc </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">!=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 3</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x26;&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> argc </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">!=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 2</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">        fprintf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(stderr, </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"Usage: </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%s</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;example-name> [&#x3C;external-btf>]</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">argv</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">[</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">]);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">        return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (argc </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">==</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 3</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">        opts.btf_custom_path </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> argv</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">[</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">2</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">];</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">    /* Set up libbpf errors and debug info callback */</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    libbpf_set_print</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(libbpf_print_fn);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">    /* Cleaner handling of Ctrl-C */</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    signal</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(SIGINT, sig_handler);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    signal</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(SIGTERM, sig_handler);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">    /* Load and verify BPF application */</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    skel </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> uprobe_bpf__open_opts</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">opts</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">!</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">skel) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">        fprintf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(stderr, </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"Failed to open and load BPF skeleton</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">        return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>This is the same usage as enabling CO-RE on older kernel versions without BTF information. Also, you need to record the data structs in the BTF info of the eBPF program, for example, if you want <code>struct data</code> to be relocated:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#define</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> BPF_NO_GLOBAL_DATA</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// #define BPF_NO_PRESERVE_ACCESS_INDEX</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;vmlinux.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;bpf/bpf_helpers.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;bpf/bpf_tracing.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#ifndef</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> BPF_NO_PRESERVE_ACCESS_INDEX</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#pragma</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> clang</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> attribute</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> push</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">__attribute__</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">((</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">preserve_access_index</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)), </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">apply_to</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> = </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">record</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#endif</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">struct</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> data {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">        int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> a;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">        int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> c;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">        int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> d;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">};</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#ifndef</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> BPF_NO_PRESERVE_ACCESS_INDEX</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#pragma</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> clang</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> attribute</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> pop</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#endif</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">SEC</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"uprobe/examples/btf-base:add_test\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> BPF_UPROBE</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(add_test, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">struct</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> data </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">d</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> a </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, c </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    bpf_probe_read_user</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">a, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">sizeof</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(a), </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">d->a);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    bpf_probe_read_user</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">c, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">sizeof</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(c), </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">d->c);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    bpf_printk</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"add_test(&#x26;d) </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%d</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> + </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%d</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> = </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%d\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, a, c,  a </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> c);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> a </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> c;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">char</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> LICENSE</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">[]</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> SEC</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"license\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> \"Dual BSD/GPL\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>In fact, the BTF implementation for relocation requires two parts: the compile-time BTF information carried by the BPF program, and the BTF information of the kernel when loading the eBPF program. When actually loading the eBPF program, libbpf will modify potentially incorrect eBPF instructions based on the accurate BTF information of the current kernel, ensuring compatibility across different kernel versions.</p>\n<p>Interestingly, libbpf does not differentiate whether these BTF information come from user-space programs or the kernel. Therefore, by merging the user-space BTF information with kernel BTF and provide them to libbpf, the problem is solved.</p>\n<p>For more details, please see our blog <a href=\"/tutorials/38-btf-uprobe/\">Expanding eBPF Compile Once, Run Everywhere(CO-RE) to Userspace Compatibility</a>. The CO-RE can also be used in kernel eBPF for userspace applications.</p>","headings":[],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/bpftime/documents/co-re.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2024-01-26T22:42:22.000Z","createdAt":"2024-01-26T22:42:22.000Z","authors":[{"name":"云微","email":"1067852565@qq.com"}]},"path":"/bpftime/documents/co-re/","alternates":{"en":"/bpftime/documents/co-re/","zh":"/zh/bpftime/documents/co-re/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"bpftime","description":"High-performance userspace eBPF runtime and extension framework for production tracing, runtime extension, and low-overhead instrumentation.","href":"/bpftime/"},"previous":{"title":"Benchmark and performance evaluation for bpftime","description":"The benchmark directory contains benchmarks and experiments for the bpftime project, including:","href":"/bpftime/documents/performance/"},"next":{"title":"bpftime Attach System","description":"The attach system in bpftime provides a modular framework for attaching eBPF programs to various event sources in userspace. It supports multiple attachment types including function probes (uprobes), syscall tracing, and","href":"/bpftime/documents/attach/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"bpftime","items":[{"title":"bpftime","href":"/bpftime/","depth":0},{"title":"Introduction","href":"/bpftime/documents/introduction/","depth":2},{"title":"Installation and Test","href":"/bpftime/documents/build-and-test/","depth":2},{"title":"Manual","href":"/bpftime/documents/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"Examples & Use Cases","href":"/bpftime/documents/examples/","depth":2},{"title":"Available kernel features in userspace","href":"/bpftime/documents/available-features/","depth":2},{"title":"Write and Run eBPF on GPU with bpftime","href":"/bpftime/documents/gpu/","depth":2},{"title":"The design and implementation of bpftime","href":"/bpftime/documents/how-it-works/","depth":2},{"title":"Benchmark and performance evaluation for bpftime","href":"/bpftime/documents/performance/","depth":2},{"title":"Compile Once, Run Everywhere(CO-RE)","href":"/bpftime/documents/co-re/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftime Attach System","href":"/bpftime/documents/attach/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftimetool","href":"/bpftime/documents/bpftimetool/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftime-aot","href":"/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot/","depth":2},{"title":"Contact and citations","href":"/bpftime/documents/contact/","depth":2},{"title":"Userspace eBPF VM with LLVM JIT/AOT Compiler","href":"/bpftime/llvmbpf/","depth":1},{"title":"EIM: Extension Interface Model","href":"/bpftime/EIM/","depth":1},{"title":"EIM: Extension Interface Model Specification","href":"/bpftime/EIM/spec/","depth":2},{"title":"UProbe Role Definition README","href":"/bpftime/EIM/uprobe/","depth":2},{"title":"EIM: Example code","href":"/bpftime/EIM/example/","depth":2},{"title":"EIM Usage and people involved (Draft v1)","href":"/bpftime/EIM/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"studies on bugs in extensions/plugins","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/","depth":2},{"title":"Study on Bugs in Browser Extensions and IDE Plugins","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/browser-ide-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"Study on Bugs in Database and Web Server Extension Interfaces","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/db-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"Study on Hypervisor and Container Extension Bugs (2018–2024)","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/docker-vm-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"Case Studies of Bugs in Productivity Software and Game Extensions/Plugins (2018–2024)","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/game-office-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Systems compare with EIM","href":"/bpftime/EIM/study/compare/","depth":3},{"title":"EIM on verify: what can it do and what cannot","href":"/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/current-EIM-lack/","depth":3},{"title":"spec_core","href":"/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec_core/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Model Specification V1","href":"/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec_old/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Inferface Model Specification V3","href":"/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec/","depth":3}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}